Citation.sTitle: Volumetric Properties and Viscosities for Aqueous NFM Solutions from 25 C to 70 C
Citation.sAbstract: This paper reports the density and viscosity of aqueous N-formyl morpholine (NFM) solutions at five temperatures in the range 25 C to 70 C over the whole concentration range. The results are compared with data published in the literature. The excess molar volumes, the partial molar volumes at infinite dilution and viscosity deviations were derived.
